Georgia Power sees nuke back later Tuesday . Georgia Power Co ' s 1 , 162 megawatt ( MW ) Vogtle 2 nuclear unit , which was manually shut late Monday , is expected to restart later today , the company said . " It ' s pretty minor . They think it will be back on - line later today , " said company spokeswoman Loretto Stevens . The unit , located in Waynesboro , Ga . , was shut due to a " malfunctioning feedwater regulator valve , " she said . Georgia Power ' s other Vogtle unit , with an identical generating capacity , is operating at full power . Georgia Power is a unit of Southern Co . - - H McCulloch , New York Power Desk + 212 - 859 - 1628 
